{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease a plastic storage container (approx. 12 - 18 cm) with oil and set aside.","Place rosemary, thyme, water, olive oil and vegetable stock paste into mixing bowl and cook <b>7 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add polenta, ground black pepper and salt and cook <b>15 min\/100°C\/speed 4<b>.","Transfer cooked polenta into prepared container and allow to cool and set.","Once set, cut polenta into chips (approx. 3 x 10 cm). Heat a large frying pan and butter over medium-high heat. Season chips with extra salt just before frying. Once pan is hot, add polenta chips and fry on both sides until lightly golden. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 tsp olive oil, plus extra for greasing","1 sprig fresh rosemary, leaves only, finely chopped","1 sprig fresh thyme, leaves only, finely chopped","480 g water","2 tsp vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","100 g polenta (cornmeal)","1 pinch ground black pepper, to taste","2 pinches salt, plus extra to taste","20 g butter, for frying"]}],"id":"r78479","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-oZIIl6DEfrQ\/XZWZ9T8HZOI\/AAAAAAAAeUE\/sf3wyje0WX44n9-MJSbVUu0Hc_5VXTS2wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_qgC65K_G-WCrZOMs.png","title":"Rosemary and thyme polenta chips","publishedAt":"2015-05-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"16 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"36 g","calories":"1318 kJ \/ 314 kcal"},"usefulItems":"plastic storage container (approx. 12 - 18 cm), turner \/ fish slice, large frying pan, oven, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or the <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","Coarse polenta may take slightly longer to cook.","Insert a spoon into your polenta to check if it is ready. Once cooked, it will leave a thick layer on both sides of the spoon.","You can serve your polenta creamy at the end of step 4 as an accompaniment to the <em>Beef spezzatino<\/em>, <em>Pork and apple cider stew<\/em> or the <em>Mediterranean vegetable bake<\/em>.<br>","<strong>Baked chips:<\/strong> Preheat oven to 200°C. Place cut chips onto a baking tray lined with baking paper, drizzle with a little olive oil and sprinkle with sea salt. Bake for 15-20 minutes (200°C) or until chips are golden."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","1h","2 portions"]}